 704.2 

Definitions.



* * * * *





Corporate credit union

 means an organization that: 

(1) Is chartered under Federal or state law as a credit union;
(2) Receives shares from and provides loan services to other credit unions;
(3) Is operated primarily for the purpose of serving other credit unions;
(4) Is designated by the National Credit Union Administration as a corporate credit union;
(5) Limits natural person members to the minimum required by state or federal law to charter and operate the credit
union; and
(6) Does not condition the eligibility of any credit union to become a member on that credit union's membership in any
other organization.



* * * * *





Trade association 

means an association of organizations or persons formed to promote their common interests. The term includes entities
owned or controlled directly or indirectly by such an association but does not include credit unions.



