 22.563

 Provision of rural radiotelephone service upon request.



Channels in the frequency ranges 152.03-152.81, 157.77-158.67, 454.025-454.650 and 459.025-459.650
MHz, inclusive, are also allocated for assignment in the Rural Radiotelephone Service. Stations in the Paging and
Radiotelephone Service that provide two-way public mobile service on these channels must also provide rural radiotelephone
service upon request from a subscriber.



 22.565 

Transmitting power limits.



The transmitting power of base, mobile and fixed transmitters operating on the channels listed in  22.561 must
not exceed the limits in this section.


